tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria), mild hypoglycemia, and mildly elevated liver enzymes. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal appearance, suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy, though blood glucose is low. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent clinical evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and further assessment of liver function and metabolic status.
